    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-10-13T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-10-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="576"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d576">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">648L.113/10a</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bingham</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 1460</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-10-13">October 13,
                            1936</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: With reference to the Embassy’s despatch No.
                    2466, dated August 18, 1936, entitled “Proposed Preferential Margin of Duty on
                    Tobacco Imported into Nigeria and the Gold Coast” there is enclosed a copy of a
                    memorandum of a conversation between Mr. Dunn and Mr. H. O. Chalkley, British
                    Commercial Counselor held September 21, 1936,<note n="4" xml:id="d576fn4">
                        <hi rend="italic">Supra</hi>.</note> on the same subject.</p>
                <p>There is also enclosed a copy of a memorandum prepared in the Bureau of
                    Agricultural Economics, Department of Agriculture,<note n="5" xml:id="d576fn5"
                        >Not printed.</note> and dealing with the West African trade in tobacco.</p>
                <p>You are requested, if opportunity presents itself, to supplement by informal
                    reference to the subject the expression of concern which has been conveyed
                    through Mr. Chalkley, and to report to the Department on the results thereof,
                    and to submit any other available information on the whole question.</p>
                <p>Very truly yours,</p>
                <closer>For the Secretary of State: <lb/>
                    <signed>R. <hi rend="smallcaps">Walton Moore</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
